$ ctria3_constrained_thermal.bdf
$ Two CTRIA3 — uniaxial constrained thermal stress (x-direction)
$
$ Geometry: 1 m × 1 m square (split by diagonal 1-3), t = 0.1 m
$ Material: E = 1e6 Pa, nu = 0.3, alpha = 1e-5 /°C
$ Load:     uniform T = 100 °C (ΔT = 100 °C, T_ref = 0)
$ BCs:      fix T1 (x) of all four nodes — plate cannot expand in x
$           fix T2 of nodes 1 and 2 — y rigid-body and rotation
$           fix T3 of nodes 1, 2, 4 — out-of-plane stability
$           Plate is free to contract/expand in y (Poisson effect)
$
$ Hand calculation (plane stress, x constrained, y free → σ_y = 0):
$   σ_x = -E*α*ΔT = -1000 Pa
$   σ_y = 0
$   von Mises = 1000 Pa
$
SOL 101
CEND
SUBCASE 1
  LABEL = CTRIA3 CONSTRAINED THERMAL
  LOAD = 1
  SPC = 1
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
  STRESS = ALL
BEGIN BULK
PARAM,CSVOUT,YES
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,1.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,3,,1.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,4,,0.0,1.0,0.0
MAT1,1,1.0E6,,0.3,0.0,1.0E-5,0.0
PSHELL,1,1,0.1
CTRIA3,1,1,1,2,3
CTRIA3,2,1,1,3,4
$ Fix T1 of all nodes — x-constraint to produce predictable thermal stress
SPC1,1,1,1
SPC1,1,1,2
SPC1,1,1,3
SPC1,1,1,4
$ Fix T2 of nodes 1 and 2 — y rigid-body and rotation suppression
SPC1,1,2,1
SPC1,1,2,2
$ Out-of-plane: fix T3, R1, R2 (DOFs 3,4,5) of all nodes.
$ Thermal expansion is purely in-plane; bending DOFs are zero by symmetry.
SPC1,1,345,1
SPC1,1,345,2
SPC1,1,345,3
SPC1,1,345,4
$ Uniform temperature T = 100 °C
TEMP,1,1,100.0
TEMP,1,2,100.0
TEMP,1,3,100.0
TEMP,1,4,100.0
ENDDATA
